{
  "texts": [
    "Contrastive learning has been used primarily in computer vision tasks [25].",
    "It has been successfully applied to various tasks, including image classification, object detection, semantic segmentation, and image generation.",
    "One of the main advantages of contrastive learning is that it does not require manual annotation of the data and thus can easily scale to large amounts of unlabeled data.",
    "Recent advances in contrastive learning methods, such as SimCLR [26] and SwAV [27], have achieved state-of-the-art performance on benchmark datasets and tasks.",
    "These results have sparked great interest in the use of contrastive learning in other domains, including natural language processing and reinforcement learning.Here, we present a novel self-supervised molecular representation for DDI prediction, SMR-DDI."
  ]
}